& [LMStudioAgentBenchmark075] is the realized local worker benchmark step
  + [moment] is the local LM Studio model needs small SOP jobs, captured output, and Codex quality review before becoming a trusted worker lane
  + [focus] is local model worker benchmark
  + [inside] is Codex operational host, provider probe, task_frame benchmark packet, lane routing packet, quality review packet, captured_output, deterministic rubric, and benchmark report
  + [boundary] is non-mutating worker evaluation hosted by Codex; local model output is proposed work until Codex reviews it
  + [outside] is automatic file mutation, local model repo authority, hidden model state, credentials, provider downtime, timeout, and broad competence claims
  + [wisdom] is the benchmark fits because it measures local lane quality before assigning real authority-bearing work
  + [caution] is local lanes remain suited for low-risk scans and proposals until repeated benchmark quality justifies more responsibility; first run found hollow-form risk in lane routing
  + [balance] is stable because Codex remains the operational host and checker while the local model remains a measured worker with usable but not yet strong aggregate quality
  + [measured_result] is openai/gpt-oss-20b scored aggregate 78 usable, with strong task-frame and quality-review behavior but failed hollow lane-routing content
  + [codex_cli_smoke_result] is codex.cmd reached LM Studio through Codex CLI local-provider mode but nested completion was blocked because n_keep 9529 was greater than or equal to n_ctx 8192
  + [boundary_blur_realization] is Honesty should penalize false access or completion claims while Caution should allow valid outside-boundary language
  + [hollow_form_realization] is Evidence should require filled content, not only named labels
  + [next_step] is compare other local LM Studio models with the same stricter rubric, then solve nested Codex CLI local-provider launch by increasing context or slimming the worker profile

  = must: capture raw model output before scoring
  = must: keep benchmark cases small and non-mutating
  = must: preserve the usable result as lane-routing data, not proof of autonomous repo authority
  = must: keep nested Codex CLI LM Studio jobs blocked until context fit is proven
  = should: compare multiple local models later using the same case set

